item.title: Is there anyone played this game?
item.dc:creator: VmKid
item.description:
I really can’t ram on Browser-Based MMOS too much because… well… my username is based on one.
Although I can’t believe that people still play Runescape. I played it for about ten minutes and stopped playing. I actually created multiple accounts because my gaps in between playings were so long I forgot my username and password. Also, one of the teachers at my school when I was nine was a bit offended by the fact that they were willing to show Christianity so much in a “Kid’s Game”. I loled.

item.title: Is there anyone played this game?
item.dc:creator: Orpheon
item.description:
A long time ago I tried to play Runescape. First something happened, then I burned some fish, and then I couldn’t figure out what to do next so I quit.

Also free-to-play MMOs don’t always suck. Perfect World was pretty fun (until they started adding stupid crap like genies), though eventually you find out that “free-to-play” also mean “pay-to-win”
